Sentencas: Developing efficient and durable cobalt-free cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) is indispensable on account of the sluggish oxygen reduction reaction (ORR).
Titulo: Oxygen vacancy-engineered cobalt-free Ruddlesden-Popper cathode with excellent CO2 tolerance for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, we report our findings in significantly improved ORR kinetics of (SrEu2)(0.9)Fe2O7-delta ((SE)(0.9)F) by introducing a 10% A-site deficiency in SrEu2Fe2O7 (SEF) at the atomic scale.
Titulo: Oxygen vacancy-engineered cobalt-free Ruddlesden-Popper cathode with excellent CO2 tolerance for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Using this cation deficient strategy, sufficient oxygen vacancy concentration in (SE)(0.9)F lattice (delta = 0.40) is successfully achieved.
Titulo: Oxygen vacancy-engineered cobalt-free Ruddlesden-Popper cathode with excellent CO2 tolerance for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, much improved electrical conductivity and promoted catalytic activity toward the ORR are observed in this new catalyst at intermediate temperatures (550-700 degrees C), which also offers excellent CO2 resistivity.
Titulo: Oxygen vacancy-engineered cobalt-free Ruddlesden-Popper cathode with excellent CO2 tolerance for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This work demonstrates an integral role of Ruddlesden-Popper oxides in applying as highly efficient and stable cobalt-free cathodes for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Oxygen vacancy-engineered cobalt-free Ruddlesden-Popper cathode with excellent CO2 tolerance for solid oxide fuel cells
